sequenceDiagram
    actor U as Usuario
    participant C as Cliente React
    participant G as API Gateway
    participant S as Community Service
    participant K as Keycloak
    participant P as PostgreSQL
    participant R as Redis

    U->>C: 1. Escribe "@juan" en barra de búsqueda
    C->>C: 2. Selecciona modo "Usuarios"
    
    C->>G: 3. GET /community/search/users?q=juan&page=1&limit=10
    Note over C,G: Authorization: Bearer {token}
    
    G->>S: 4. Proxy → /community/search/users
    
    S->>K: 5. Introspect token
    K-->>S: userInfo (postgresId)
    
    S->>R: 6. GET community:users:search:juan:1:10
    
    alt Cache HIT
        R-->>S: usuarios (JSON)
        S-->>C: 200 OK (usuarios)
        C-->>U: Mostrar resultados
    else Cache MISS
    
        S->>P: 7. SELECT * FROM search_users_trgm('juan', 1, 10)
        Note over S,P: Función PL/pgSQL con pg_trgm:
        Note over S,P: - Compara username, display_name, first_name, last_name
        Note over S,P: - Usa operador % (similitud trigrama)
        Note over S,P: - Ordena por similitud DESC
        
        P-->>S: usuarios (id, username, displayName, avatar, bio, followersCount, postsCount, similarity)
        
        S->>R: 8. SETEX community:users:search:juan:1:10 (TTL 120s)
        
        S-->>C: 9. 200 OK (usuarios)
        C-->>U: 10. Mostrar usuarios encontrados
    end